The paper deals with biometric recognition using images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of multiple algorithms and fusion techniques suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.MM) and statistical learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the potential for variations in imaging bands, which falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.CR). Finally, the experiments involve the use of smartphones, which could be classified under information retrieval (cs.IR) or human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
